{
  "stem": "15768.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My mother's youngest brother was in the United States since 1933, and he had sponsored us and put all that on track.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But since it was a fairly high number, it wasn't anywheres near being called, and therefore, we were in the situation.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There was a very wonderful Christian business associate of my father's--",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And his name is Herbert Kramer, who lived in-- in Aachen, and a wonderful woman by the name of Christina Bianbaer, a young woman.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this business associate, Herbert, made it his business to help my mother.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he went with her to the official places to get information as to where my father was.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then, on a somewhat [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] invented or manufactured excuse, he said he needed my father for his signature and the signing over of the factory to whoever it was going to go to.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so he was released from Buchenwald on the basis of this-- this-- this legal transaction.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That release was actually early in November.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It came just in time for his birthday.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the year?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was released in 1938, November of 1938.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And had he not appeared so totally broken and totally emotionally beaten, that it would have been a nice birthday present.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But in essence-- when I-- I only saw him very briefly on that occasion, and his head was shaved, and his teeth had been extracted, and he was scarred.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he spoke very, very little.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In fact, at first I really didn't recognize him when I saw him.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then after the signing, this business associate, who had dual citizenship in Belgium, literally smuggled him out of the country.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And being close to the Belgian border, it was fairly easy.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
